This is a project prepared and ready for the official Sailfish SDK. However,
to build the project, you need to load the "openssl-devel" package into the
build environment:

 1. Make sure you have a working internet connection, as the package is pulled
    from the internet.
 2. Start QTCreator from the SDK, and open the project.
 3. Start the build engine.
 4. Click the "Sailfish OS" icon (fifth from the top).
 5. Click on "manage" for the i486 target.
 6. Type "openssl-devel" into the search field.
 7. Click the "install" check box, then the "install" button.
 8. Wait until the task has been reported as successful.
 9. Click "clear".
10. Repeat steps 5 - 9 for the arm target.

